  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Placement of a vaginal pessary reduces significantly the rate of spontaneous preterm birth in
      pregnant women with short cervical length at 18-22 weeks scan.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This trial includes pregnant women undergoing routine ultrasound examination at 18.0 to 22.6
      weeks of gestation.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
